cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to extract biomolecular interactions from biomedical text. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category as well. The paper also discusses graph kernel learning, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with information retrieval techniques, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible category as well.
